The Latin America Collagen Market was valued at US$ 542 million in 2024 and is projected to reach US$ 760 million by 2030, at a CAGR of 5.8% during the forecast period 2024-2030.

Collagen represents a crucial protein-based ingredient used across multiple industries including healthcare, cosmetics, and food & beverages. It encompasses various types such as Type I, II, III, and marine collagen, available in different forms including powder, liquid, and capsules. The category includes both native and hydrolyzed collagen products, manufactured under specific conditions to maintain protein integrity and bioavailability for various applications.

